Indian Equities: Cairn, CESC, Gitanjali, Larsen, Tata Motors

-- B y   A m e y a   K a r v e
-- 
2011-02-11T11:50:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-11/indian-equities-cairn-cesc-gitanjali-larsen-tata-motors.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Indian trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 3.30 p.m. close in Mumbai.    India ’s Bombay Stock Exchange’s Sensitive Index, or Sensex,
rose 265.57, or 1.5 percent, to 17,728.61.    Cairn India Ltd . (CAIR IN) rose 3.7 percent, the most in a
month, to 325.85 rupees. The operator of India’s biggest onshore
oilfield said its net income, including that of units, surged
almost sevenfold to 20.1 billion rupees ($440 million) in the
three months ended Dec. 31. Cairn India’s rating was raised at
BNP Paribas, Macquarie and IIFL after the earnings.    CESC Ltd . (CESC IN) surged 8.2 percent, the most in nearly
22 months, to 296.35 rupees. The utility controlled by Indian
billionaire Rama Prasad Goenka may sell a stake in a unit to a
private equity firm to raise part of the $7.7 billion it plans
to spend to boost capacity sevenfold by 2017, Vice Chairman
Sanjiv Goenka said in a phone interview yesterday.    Coal India Ltd . (COAL IN) gained 2.3 percent to 304.6
rupees. The environment ministry will expedite Coal India’s
projects, Alok Perti, special secretary in the coal ministry,
told reporters in New Delhi yesterday. Separately, International
Coal Ventures Ltd., a group of five Indian state-run companies
in which Coal India has a 28 percent stake, may bid for  BHP
Billiton Ltd .’s coal prospecting rights in  South Africa ,
International Coal Ventures General Manager Ajay Mathur said.    Gitanjali Gems Ltd . (GITG IN) jumped 19 percent to 226.05
rupees, its highest close in more than 15 months. The private
equity arm of LVMH Moet Hennessy Louis Vuitton SA plans to buy a
minority stake in a proposed new unit of the Indian company in a
deal worth as much as $125 million, the Economic Times reported,
citing two unidentified people involved in the transaction. “
“Though many global players and private equity funds have shown
interest in the company” the stake sale report is
“speculation,” the Gitanjali Gems said in a statement to the
Bombay Stock Exchange today.    Larsen & Toubro Ltd . (LT IN) advanced 4.3 percent, the most
in more than months, to 1,556.1 rupees. The country’s biggest
engineering company and European Aeronautic Defence and Space
Co.’s Cassidian unit yesterday said Indian authorities have
approved the formation of their joint venture in the defense
electronics market.    Tata Motors Ltd . (TTMT IN) climbed 3.7 percent to 1,142.7
rupees. The owner of Jaguar Land Rover said third-quarter net
income more than tripled to 24.2 billion rupees in the three
months ended Dec. 31.  To contact the reporter on this story:
